<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ910614-0128</DOCNO><DOCID>910614-0128.</DOCID><HL>   International:   Asahi Chemical Industry Plant</HL><DATE>06/14/91</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE A6</SO><CO>   J.ASC</CO><MS>BASIC MATERIALS (BSC)TECHNOLOGY (TEC)</MS><IN>CHEMICALS, PLASTICS (CHM)SEMICONDUCTORS, INTEGRATED CHIPS (SEM)</IN><RE>FAR EAST (FE)JAPAN (JA)PACIFIC RIM (PRM)</RE><LP>   TOKYO -- Asahi Chemical Industry Co. said it will build asemiconductor plant in Japan in its first attempt tomass-produce large scale integration chips.   The major Japanese maker of synthetic fibers, which hasbeen expanding into nonchemical fields, will soon begin theconstruction of the plant in southern Japan. Investment isexpected to total 50 billion yen ($353.7 million), officialssaid. Production is slated to start in December 1993.</LP><TEXT>   Plans call for the new plant to have capacity to produce550 sheets a day of six-inch silicon wafers by 1995 or 1996.Officials expect sales of 50 billion yen in 1996.</TEXT></DOC>